sql:
SELECT achievement_name, date_unlocked
FROM achievements
WHERE user_id = 0;

SELECT puzzle_name, creator, difficulty_level
FROM puzzles
WHERE difficulty_level > 2;

SELECT user_id, username
FROM users
WHERE user_id NOT IN (
    SELECT DISTINCT user_id
    FROM puzzle_attempts
);

SELECT user_id, AVG(time_spent) AS average_time_spent
FROM puzzle_attempts
GROUP BY user_id;

external_knowledge:
- "frequent puzzle solvers" refers to users who have solved a minimum of 5 puzzles;
- "a handful of challenges" specifically means each user has solved at least 5 puzzles;
- "under a relatively short time" means the average time spent solving each puzzle is less than or equal to 10 minutes;
- "spent more than a significant amount of time on the platform" implies users have spent more than 100 minutes in total solving puzzles.

sql:
SELECT puzzle_name, unlock_time, solve_time
FROM puzzles
WHERE puzzle_id = 0;

SELECT user_id
FROM users
WHERE user_id NOT IN (
    SELECT user_id 
    FROM puzzle_attempts
);

SELECT total_time_spent 
FROM user_stats 
WHERE user_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- Players refer to users; 
- Spent more time than the average player refers to users whose total time spent is included in the result if their average solve time is greater than the average solve time of all users;
- Shown a slower pace in solving puzzles than the usual pace means the average solve time of the user is higher than the overall average solve time.

sql:
SELECT * 
FROM leaderboards 
WHERE user_id = (SELECT user_id FROM users WHERE username = 'puzzlefan2');

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) 
FROM puzzle_attempts 
WHERE completion_status = 'success' AND time_spent < 30;

SELECT puzzle_id, average_solve_time
FROM puzzle_stats
ORDER BY average_solve_time DESC;
